  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."]},{"name":"Mechtilde","meanings":["from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mathilde was born about 1060, in Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France. She had at least 5 sons with Hasculf FitzEudo De Saint Hilaire Du Harcouët."},"et":{"about 1060–":"umbes 1060–Surnud","1058–1130":"1058–1130","1087–Male":"1087–Surnud","1090–Male":"1090–Surnud","1090–1168":"1090–1168","1095–Male":"1095–Surnud","1097–1154":"1097–1154","1060–Female":"1060–Surnud","about 1060":"umbes 1060","1090":"1090","1154":"1154","1087":"1087","1097":"1097","1130":"1130","1095":"1095","1060":"1060","ABT 1095":"umbes 1095","1168":"1168","1058":"1058","about 1097":"umbes 1097","aft 1090":"pärast 1090","Gernon Castle, Nord-Pas-De-Calais, France":"Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","St-James-de-Beuvron, Manche, Normandy, France":"Saint-James, Basse-Normandie, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa","St.-James-de-Beuvron, Manche, Normandy, France":"Manche, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","St. Hillarie-du-Harcort, Manche, Normandy, France":"Manche, Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"about 1060–":"noin 1060–Kuollut","1058–1130":"1058–1130","1087–Male":"1087–Kuollut","1090–Male":"1090–Kuollut","1090–1168":"1090–1168","1095–Male":"1095–Kuollut","1097–1154":"1097–1154","1060–Female":"1060–Kuollut","about 1060":"noin 1060","1090":"1090","1154":"1154","1087":"1087","1097":"1097","1130":"1130","1095":"1095","1060":"1060","ABT 1095":"noin 1095","1168":"1168","1058":"1058","about 1097":"noin 1097","aft 1090":"1090 jälkeen","Gernon Castle, Nord-Pas-De-C